cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.ET, cs.SE

The paper proposes a data-driven polynomial nonlinear state-space model for lithium ion batteries, which involves the use of machine learning techniques and signal processing methods. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of nonparametric frequency domain characterization and quantification of the battery's behavior, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the modeling and analysis of battery behavior, which is relevant to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category.
